aching to the Bronze level  Shooting  Ramita Jindal have qualified for the finals in women's 10m air rifle. Arjun Babuta have qualified 4th for men's 10m air rifle inParis Olympics 2024  Prithviraj Tondaiman, Sarabjot Singh, Arjun Cheema, Manu Bhaker, Rhythm Sangwan, Arjun Babuta, and Ramita Jindal will participate in theOlympic shooters final  Lakhya Senhas won asSatwiksairaj RankireddyandChirag Shettyqualifies the Indian men's badminton doubles.  Dhiraj Bommadevara, Tarundeep Rai and Parvin Jadhav will be in theArchery teamin men's will be in the quarterfinal againstTurkey  Arjun Babutamissed his medal in the 10m air rifle men's final.  Rhythm SangwanandArjun Singh Cheemahas goal out.  Women's 10m air final Ramita Jindalsecured7th positionin the final  Hockey men's  Harmanpreet Singhhas a late scoring of1-1draw against Argentina  Manu Bhaker and Sarbjot Singhis ready to play and give a tough againstKoreain the mixed 10m air pistol shooting in the Paris Olympics 2024  Manika Batrareached the round16in Table Tennis Olympics  Men's synchronized platform diving ,Tom Daleythe British diver achieved his5th Olympic medal  Schedule Today Olympics 2024 in Paris  In Trap Men's Qualification( Indian Standard Time)  12:30pmPrithviraj Tondaiman  In Trap Women's Qualification  12:30pmRajeshwari Kumari and Shreyasi Singh  10m Air Pistol Mixed Team Bronze Medal Match  1pmManu Bhaker and Sahrabjot will play against Korea  Rowing  1:40 pmBalraj Panwar in men's single sculls quarterfinal  10m Air Pistol Mixed  There is a second medal win over byManu BhakerandSarabjyot Singh.  Bhakar has won twoBronze medaledging South Korea in 10m Air Pistol Mixed Team today  Men's Trap  Qualification Round  Prithviraj Tondaiman finished in 21st position  Women's Archery Individual  Bhajan Kaur reached round of 16  Rowing Men's Single Scull quarterfinal  Balraj Panwar finished 5th  Men's Hockey Team  India will take on Ireland  Boxing  Amit Panghal, Jasmine Lamboria and Preeti Pawar will on the stage soon  India Vrs Ireland in Men's Hockey  India wins 2-0 over Ireland. Harmanpreet Singhs scored the penalty stroke in 11th minute and then scored again in 19th minute thus leading over by hitting the goal twice  Today on the 5th day of Olympics in Paris 2024will perform on the stage  Shuttler  PV Sindhu  Archer  Deepika Kumari  Boxer  Lovlina Borgohain  Lovelina Borgohain will open the campaign today  Men's Rifle 50m  Aishwary Pratap Singh Tomar and  Swapnil Kusale  Shooter\\u00a0Swapnil Kusale has clinched the bronze medal in the men's 50m rifle 3 positions final held at the National Shooting Center in Ch\\u00e2teauroux on Thursday.  The 29-year-old from Kambalwadi village near Kolhapur in Maharashtra finished in third place with 195 in standing after 156.8 in the prone and 153.3 in the kneeling rounds.  By doing so, he has etched his name in history by becoming the first Indian shooter to win an Olympic medal in the men's 50m rifle 3 positions event.  Serbian tennis star Novak Djokovic's bid for Olympic gold could come to an abrupt end as the uncertainty over his further participating in the ongoing Paris Olympics looms large due to a knee injury.  Djokovic said he was \\\"hoping for the best\\\" after aggravating his injured right knee, which had required surgery in June, during his 6-3, 7-6 (7/3) win over Stefanos Tsitsipas in the quarter-finals.  The 37-year-old needed on-court treatment and a painkiller after slipping on the baseline of Court Philippe Chatrier.  Manu Bhaker has stepped closer to an unprecedented third medal of the ongoing Paris Games after qualifying for the final of 25m Pistol women's event.  Manu shot 294 in the precision stage of the qualifiers and followed that up with an emphatic 296 in the rapid stage. She thus finished with a total score of 590 out of a possible 600.  India pulled off an incredible upset against heavyweights Australia in their final Pool B match on August 2.  India stunned Australia in a thrilling 3-2 victory to win their final group game and enter the quarterfinals on a high.  By doing so, India also ended a 52-year wait for a win over Australia in the Olympics. This is also the first win for India against Australia since AstroTurf was introduced in Olympics.  Indian archers Ankita Bhakat and Dhiraj Bommadevara advanced to the quarterfinals of the mixed team event after defeating Indonesia's Diananda Choirunisa and Arif Pangestu in the round of 16 on Friday.  The Indian duo secured a 5-1 victory (37-36, 38-38, 38-37) at the Invalides. The fifth seeds hit five tens in their pre-quarterfinal win at Les Invalides.  Skeet Mixed Team (Qualification): Maheshwari Chauhan and Anant Jeet Singh Naruka -- 12.30 pm  Women's Team (Pre-quarterfinal): India vs Romania -- 1.30 pm  Women's Dinghy (Opening series): Race 9 -- 3.45 pm  Women's Dinghy (Opening series): Race 10 -- 4.53 pm  Men's Dinghy (Opening series): Race 9 -- 6.10 pm  Men's Dinghy (Opening series): Race 10 -- 7.15 pm  Women's 400m (Round 1): Kiran Pahal (Heat 5) -- 3.57 pm  Men's 3,000m Steeplechase (Round 1): Avinash Sable (Heat 2) -- 10.50 pm  Men's Singles (Bronze medal playoff): Lakshya Sen vs Zii Jia Lee (Malaysia) -- 6.00 pm  The Indian men's hockey team led by skipper Harmanpreet Singh will take on world champions Germany in an exciting semi-final clash in Paris.  India and Germany have played 18 matches against each other so far with India leading the head to head 8-6. 4 matches have finished in draws.  India, who had clinched the bronze medal in Tokyo 2020 by beating the same opponent, will be looking to seal their berth in the final after 44 years.  The match will be played on August 6, Tuesday at 10:30 PM IST and can be viewed live on Sports 18 1 and Sports 18 2 channels and live streamed on JioCinema app and website.  Star shooter Manu Bhaker has been chosen as India's flag-bearer for the closing ceremony of the Paris Olympics 2024.  Manu expressed her gratitude and said she was honoured to be given the responsibility.  She scripted history by winning two Olympic medals in a single edition of the Olympics. The 22-year-old\\u00a0shooter from Haryana joined an elite list including PV Sindhu and Norman Pritchard to have secured two medals in the Olympics.  The closing ceremony of the Paris Olympics 2024 will be held on August 11, Sunday.  India's badminton sensation Lakshya Sen will battle it out against Lee Zii Jia\\u00a0of Malaysia for the bronze\\u00a0medal today in the men's singles event.  He will look to bounce back from his heartbreaking semi-final defeat at the hands of reigning Olympic Champion Viktor Axelsen yesterday despite a spirited fight.  All hopes will rest on his shoulders to bring home India's fourth medal and the first in Badminton in this edition.  India's full schedule on Day 11 of Paris Olympics:  Men's Team (Pre-quarterfinal): India (Harmeet Desai, Sharath Kamal and Manav Thakkar) vs China -- 1.30 pm  Men's Javelin Throw (Qualification): Kishore Jena -- 1.50 pm  Men's Javelin Throw (Qualification): Neeraj Chopra -- 3.20 pm  Women's 400m (Repechage): Kiran Pahal -- 2.50 pm  Vinesh Phogat (50kg) vs Japan's Yui Susaki in pre-quarters at 2.30 pm.  Men's semi-final: India vs Germany -- 10.30 pm.  India's golden boy and Tokyo Gold medalist Neeraj Chopra stormed into the finals of the men's javelin event after his first attempt, which also happened to be his season-best effort.  Neeraj's throw was clocked at an impressive 89.34m as the reigning Olympic champion spent just 10 minutes on the field at the Stade de France on Tuesday.  Indian wrestler Vinesh Phogat has made it to the quarter-finals of thewomen's 50kg category on Tuesday.  She caused a major upset by beating defending champion Yui Susaki of Japan 3-2 in the Round of 16.  Vinesh Phogat, who is riding high on confidence after beating defending champion Yui Susaki in the previous round, knocked out Oksana Livach of Ukraine to seal her berth in the semi-finals of the women's 50kg category on Tuesday.  The Indian wrestler won by a scoreline of 7-5 to get one step close at a podium finish.  Phogat will face Cuba's Yusneylys Guzman in the semi-finals today.  Vinesh Phogat has been disqualified from the Paris Olympics after she could not make the weight on the morning of her 50 kg gold medal bout.  As per sources, wrestler was roughly 100 grams over the permissible limits, which could lead to her disqualification. According to competition rules, Phogat will not be eligible even for a silver medal and the 50 kg will have just gold and bronze medal winners.  India's shooting sensation Manu Bhaker received a rousing welcome after landing in India on\\u00a0Wednesday.  She was welcomed by hundreds of supporters and her family, who braved a steady drizzle to give her a memorable reception in New Delhi.  The 22-year-old Bhaker won a bronze each in the women's 10m air pistol and 10m air pistol mixed team event -- where she had paired with Sarabjot Singh -- to script Olympic history for the country.  Wrestler Vinesh Phogat was hospitalised on August 7 in Paris just minutes after she was disqualified from the women's 50kg final at the Paris Olympics.  As per sources, the Olympian fainted due to dehydration. Phogat was disqualified as she was 150 grams overweight during the weigh-in on the second day of the competition.  Currently, Vinesh is in the polyclinic of the Olympic Village, where she is stable and resting.  Antim Panghal lost her opening bout against Zeynep Yetgil of Turkey in the round of 16 of the women's freestyle 53kg event.  Despite the defeat with a final score of 0-10, Panghal's campaign at Paris 2024 is not over yet.  She still has a chance to compete in the repechage round if Yetgil advances to the final.  Indian women's\\u00a0table tennis\\u00a0team lost to Germany 1-3 in the quarterfinal of the\\u00a0Paris 2024 Olympics\\u00a0on Wednesday.  Archana Kamath's 3-1 win against Shan Xiaona was India's saving grace in the match with the other three matches ending in losses.  Here is India's schedule of Day 13 of competitions at the ongoing Paris Olympics on Thursday, August 8  Women's Individual Strokeplay Round 2: Aditi Ashok and Diksha Dagar - 12:30 pm  Women's 100m hurdles Repechage Round (Heat 1): Jyothi Yarraji - 2:05 pm  Men's javelin throw final:Neeraj Chopra- 11:55 pm  Men's 57kg freestyle round of 16: Aman Sehrawat - 2:30 pm  Men's 57 kg freestyle quarter-finals (If qualified): Aman Sehrawat - 4:20 pm  Men's 57 kg freestyle semi-finals (If qualified): Aman Sehrawat -9:45 pm onwards  Women's 57kg freestyle round of 16: Anshu Malik - 2:30 pm  Women's 57kg freestyle quarter-finals (If qualified): Anshu Malik -4:20 pm  Women's 57kg freestyle semi-finals (If qualified): Anshu Malik - 10:25 pm onwards  Men's Bronze medal match:India vs Spain - 5:30 pm  The Indian Men's Hockey team will battle it out against Spain for the bronze medal at the Paris Olympics.  The 'Men in Blue' will look to secure India's fourth medal at the quadrennial event after the country's medal hopes suffered a series of setbacks of late.  The India vs Spain hockey bronze medal match will be played at the Yves-du-Manoir Stadium, Paris at 5:30 PM IST.  The match will be available for free live streaming on the Jio Cinema app and website. Indians can also watch the live telecast of the match at Sports18.  India's medal prospect Neeraj Chopra will look to defend his Olympic crown when he takes the track in the men's javelin throw final.  The Tokyo Gold medalist will look to push India's stagnant medal tally. His title defence will start at 11:55 pm today.  INDIA'S FULL SCHEDULE IN PARIS OLYMPICS: AUGUST 9  Golf - Women's Individual Stroke Play Round 3 (Aditi Ashok, Diksha Dagar)  2:10 PM IST  Athletics - Women's 4x400m Relay Round 1 Heat 2 (Jyothika Sri Dandi, Kiran Pahal, Poovamma Raju, Vithya Ramraj, Subha Venkatesan)  2:35 PM IST  Athletics - Men's 4x400m Relay Round 1 Heat 2 (Amol Jacob, Rajesh Ramesh, Santhosh Kumar, Muhammed Ajmal, Muhammed Anas)  Wrestling - Men's Freestyle 57kg Bronze Medal Match (Aman Sehrawat)  All eyes will be focused on Aman Sehrawat as the Indian wrestler will battle it out for the bronze medal in the men's 57kg wrestling category.  Aman started-off well in this tournament by emerging victorious in his first two bouts owing to technical superiority but he was eventually knocked out by Japan's Rei Higuchi in the semi-finals.  Indian wrestler Reetika Hooda lost to top seed Aiperi Medet Kyzy of Kyrgyzstan in quarterfinals of Women's 76kg event at Paris Olympics.  This comes after Reetika defeated Hungary's Bernadett Nagy in the Round of 16. Reetika will now have to rely on the repechage round to win a medal.  Follow Us  \\u00a9 sentinelassam-english 2025  Powered byQuintype\"}"